{"model": "Qwen 3 32B", "runtime": "mlx", "prompt_name": "logic_ages__t3_cot", "prompt_tokens": 94, "generation_tokens": 1459, "prompt_tps": 279.6994368927157, "generation_tps": 26.52337604162091, "peak_memory_gb": 19.786932916, "wall_time_sec": 55.40339020799729, "output": "Let Bob's current age be $ B $. Since Alice is twice as old as Bob, Alice's current age is $ 2B $. In 10 years, Bob will be $ B + 10 $ years old, and Alice will be $ 2B + 10 $ years old. According to the problem, at that future time, Alice's age will be 1.5 times Bob's age:\n\n$$\n2B + 10 = 1.5(B + 10)\n$$\n\nExpanding the right-hand side:\n\n$$\n2B + 10 = 1.5B + 15\n$$\n\nSubtracting $ 1.5B $ from both sides:\n\n$$\n0.5B + 10 = 15\n$$\n\nSubtracting 10 from both sides:\n\n$$\n0.5B = 5\n$$\n\nSolving for $ B $:\n\n$$\nB = \\frac{5}{0.5} = 10\n$$\n\nVerification confirms correctness: Bob is currently 10 years old, Alice is 20 years old. In 10 years, Bob will be 20 and Alice will be 30, satisfying the condition $ 30 = 1.5 \\times 20 $. \n\nANSWER: 10", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "a33ec0efd7f9", "quant": "4bit"}
